<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8346066>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Echiniscus granulatus from France (PCM): A—female in dorsolateral view (neotype, arrowheads indicate weakly developed pedal plates), B—juvenile in dorsolateral view, C—larva in dorsal view. Scale bars = 50 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8346066/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8346068>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Echiniscus granulatus from France (females in dorsal view): A—PCM (arrowhead indicates an asymmetric lack of spine Cd), B—SEM. Scale bars = 50 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8346068/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8346072>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Echiniscus granulatus from France (dorsal plate sculpturing):A—female in dorsal view (SEM), B—scapular plate (PCM), C—paired segmental plate 1 (SEM). Scale bars in μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8346072/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8346074>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Echiniscus granulatus from France (claws): A—claws III (PCM), B—claws III (SEM). Scale bars = 10 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8346074/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8346076>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Newly established synonyms of E. granulatus (PCM): A—E. heterospinosus syn. nov. (holotype), B—scapular plate of E. egnatiae syn. nov. (paratype), C—paired segmental plate I of E. egnatiae syn. nov. (paratype), D—caudal plate of E. egnatiae syn. nov. (paratype). Scale bars = 10 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8346076/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8346078>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Minimum spanning haplotype networks for the granulatus complex (circles:E. granulatus, triangles:E. militaris): A—ITS-1, B—ITS-2. The size of circles/triangles is correlated with the number of individuals representing a single haplotype. Small black circles represent putative (non-sampled/extinct) haplotypes required to join the detected haplotypes. The numbers at connecting lines indicate the number of mutations between the haplotypes." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8346078/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

